@startuml system-context
'' ============================================================================
'' vinary-viewer — System Context (C4 Level 1)
''
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because: C4-PlantUML gives first-class `Person`/`System`/
'' `System_Ext` actors with a trust-boundary `enclosure` and a self-contained
'' `legend` keyed to our per-concept palette — Mermaid's flowchart has no native
'' C4 vocabulary and cannot reproduce the colour-means-one-concept discipline that
'' the rest of this suite relies on.
'' ============================================================================
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title vinary-viewer — System Context

skinparam actorStyle awesome
skinparam rectangle {
  BorderThickness 1.6
  FontColor #1A1A1A
}

actor "User\n(reads docs, edits\nin a separate editor)" as User #white

rectangle "vinary-viewer\n(Electron desktop app)\n— reactive document previewer" as App RENDERER_COLOR {
}

rectangle "External Editor\n(Emacs, VS Code, Vim …)" as Editor <<actor>> FS_COLOR
rectangle "Filesystem\n(Markdown / images / text\non disk)" as FS FS_COLOR
rectangle "git repository\n(`git ls-files` →\nfile-tree sidebar)" as Git FS_COLOR

User --> App : launches `vv README.md`,\nclicks tabs / tree / TOC,\nfinds, switches theme
Editor --> FS : saves the file\nthe user is editing
App --> FS : **reads** file content;\n**watches** each open path\n(chokidar)
FS ..> App : `change` / `add` events\n⟶ live refresh
App --> Git : `git rev-parse` +\n`git ls-files`
Git ..> App : repo root + tracked files

note right of App
  vinary-viewer is **read-only** with respect to
  user content: it never writes the documents it
  previews. Editing happens in the user's own editor;
  the viewer reflects every save automatically.
end note

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  | <#2D9574> | the vinary-viewer application |
  | <#9F8766> | filesystem · external editor · git |
  | <#FFFFFF> | human actor |
  Solid arrow = request / command · Dashed = asynchronous event
endlegend
@enduml
